## Requirements:
- Create a clock that displays time in 24hr and 12hr format based on user input
# Flow:
- Run application
  - Get local machine's time, do not display it
- Get user input for current time
  - Display user's machine time, ask if they would like to use it
  - if user inputs no time, default to current system time
  - Get input for hour, minute, seconds if no
- Display current time and possible commands
  - command inputs
    - 1 - Add 1 Hour
      - hour++
      - display time
      - display command menu
    - 2 - Add 1 Minute
      - minute++
      - display time
      - display menu
    - 3 - Add 1 Second
      - second++
      - display time
      - display menu
    - 4 - Exit
      - terminate program

## Implementation:
# Display:
 - displayTime
 - displayCommand
# Clock:
 - time
   - hour
   - min
   - sec
 - CommandGate(input after initial phase)
   - getInput
   - processInput
   - chooseClockCommand